# Guru99 Bank Automation Testing

A Selenium-based test automation framework developed for the Guru99 Bank demo application. This project demonstrates the implementation of automated functional testing using Java, Selenium WebDriver, TestNG, and the Page Object Model (POM) design pattern.

## Project Overview

This project was developed as a collaborative academic project with the goal of applying Software Testing principles and QA Automation practices to a real-world banking system simulation.

The framework automates critical banking workflows, including:

* Login
* Customer Management
* Account Creation
* Deposit
* Withdrawal
* Fund Transfer
* Customized Statement
* Logout

In addition to automation testing, a comprehensive manual testing process was conducted, resulting in 60 documented test cases covering positive, negative, validation, and business workflow scenarios.

---

## Technologies Used

* Java
* Selenium WebDriver
* TestNG
* Page Object Model (POM)
* Maven
* Git & GitHub
* WebDriverManager

---

## Framework Architecture

The project follows the Page Object Model (POM) design pattern to improve maintainability and reusability.

### Structure

```text
src
├── main
│   └── java
│       └── pages
│           ├── LoginPage
│           ├── ManagerHomePage
│           ├── NewCustomerPage
│           ├── NewAccountPage
│           ├── DepositPage
│           ├── WithdrawPage
│           ├── FundTransferPage
│           └── CustomizedStatementPage
│
└── test
    └── java
        ├── base
        │   └── BaseTest
        │
        └── tests
            ├── LoginTest
            ├── CustomerTest
            ├── AccountTest
            ├── DepositTest
            ├── WithdrawTest
            ├── FundTransferTest
            ├── StatementTest
            └── LogoutTest
```

---

## Key Features

### Manual Testing

* Designed and documented 60 test cases.
* Covered positive and negative test scenarios.
* Performed validation testing and workflow testing.
* Documented expected and actual results for each test case.

### Automation Testing

* Automated 8 core banking modules.
* Implemented reusable Page Objects.
* Utilized dynamic XPath and CSS selectors.
* Centralized WebDriver setup using a reusable BaseTest class.
* Implemented alert handling and synchronization using Selenium waits.
* Executed assertions using TestNG.

